        {
            "review_id": "225274034",
            "steam_id": "76561198831081578",
            "playtime_minutes": 2163,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 3,
            "weighted_score": 0.5546558499336243,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "I love this game. It is special to me, as I have played it for far longer than it shows (having pirated it many years ago).\nThis is the first game I have ever bought. Also the first to get all achievements. I also bought it for my brother, even though we often play splitscreen :P\nVery easy to run, a lot of fun whether solo or co-op and even many years later, the developers release updates to improve the game. The workshop is quite rich in content, the gameplay is fantastic, the controls are intuitive and easy to understand, anyone could pick this game up and enjoy it\n\nOverall, a solid RECOMMEND. Tons of hours of gameplay, and when the game is on sale, it's quite simply the best deal you can get. Another big bonus is the capacity for splitscreen, too few co-op games nowadays include it!"
        },
