        {
            "review_id": "226658880",
            "steam_id": "76561199130749446",
            "playtime_minutes": 1850,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "It isn't too serious, the mechanics are wobbly and comical, the general difficulty is at a good level for kids to play and effort has gone into level design with nice little puzzles to work through.\nI like the splitscreen feature and wish more games had this option, there's something about playing together side-by-side that adds to the enjoyment of the game.\nThe steam workshop levels are also a very pleasant surprise. These extra levels made by the players are easy to add into the game and play through. I expect we'll spend a lot of additional hours in this one because there are so many to choose from."
        },
