        {
            "review_id": "225536016",
            "steam_id": "76561198998774550",
            "playtime_minutes": 229,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 0,
            "weighted_score": 0.5,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "After playing Human: Fall Flat, I can say it is one of the funniest and most entertaining co-op games to play with friends. The physics-based gameplay creates nonstop hilarious moments, especially when players accidentally fall, grab the wrong objects, or completely fail simple tasks in the funniest ways possible. The puzzles are creative and give players freedom to solve them in different ways, which makes exploration and teamwork very enjoyable. The simple graphics and goofy character movements add a lot of charm to the experience. Sometimes the controls can feel clumsy and frustrating, but that chaos is also what makes the game so fun and memorable. Overall, Human: Fall Flat is a great casual game for relaxing, laughing with friends, and enjoying creative puzzle gameplay."
        },
